# API base URL (see also `.env.development` and `.env.production`).
#
# Development (`npm run dev`) — default in `.env.development`:
#   - `VITE_API_URL=` (empty) → relative `/api/...` and Vite proxies to http://localhost:3001
#   - Start backend: `cd backend && npm start` (PORT=3001)
#
# Development against Railway instead:
#   - In `.env.development` set `VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend.up.railway.app`
#
# Direct local API (no proxy):
#   - `VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3001`
#
# Production build (`npm run build`):
#   Set Railway (or your API) in `.env.production` or on Vercel/Netlify env vars.

# Google Analytics (gtag.js) is loaded from `frontend/index.html` (measurement ID G-5WLK785TPH).
# To use a different ID, edit the two script blocks in that file.
